{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the High Income Child Benefit Charge threshold in line with inflation ",
        "additional_details": "In 2013 the High Income Child Benefit Charge was introduced, with the target of recuperating child benefit paid to families where one or more parents were classed as 'high earners'. \r\n \r\nAt this time, \u00a350,000 was deemed as the lower threshold for a high earner. In 2023, this limit remains unchanged despite inflation. \r\n \r\nAs a result the current HICBC penalises working families who no longer fall within the 'high earner' category.\r\n",
        "background": "The Government should increase the High Income Child Benefit Charge threshold in line with inflation since this was set in 2013. ",
